   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>THE TRIUNE GOD'S REVELATION AND HIS MOVE MESSAGE ONE THE TRIUNE GOD, HIS WORD, HIS REVELATION, HIS VISION, AND HIS MOVE Scripture Reading: Matt 28:19; Heb 1:1-2; 2 Tim 3:16; Eph 1:17; Acts 26:19; 1 Tim 1:4; Eph 1:10; 3:9 OUTLINE The Triune God: The source of the divine revelation.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Revealed as the Triune God in the divine revelation throughout the whole Scriptures Matt 28:19.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>The Triune God's word: The speaking God Heb 1:1-2.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>The Triune God's speaking became His written word the holy Scriptures 2 Tim 3:16.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>The Triune God's revelation: The Triune God's word contains and conveys His divine revelation.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Through His Spirit Eph 1:17.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>The Triune God's vision: When the divine light shines over the divine revelation, the divine revelation becomes the divine vision Acts 26:19.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>The Spirit of revelation gives us the sight to see the vision and understand it with His wisdom Eph 1:17.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>The Triune God's move: The Triune God moves in and according to His divine revelation.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>For the accomplishment of His eternal economy 1 Tim 1:4; Eph 1:10; 3:9.</S>
   </TEXT>
